{
  "texts": [
    "SH: Be careful not to conflate the HP with the Other-Minds-Problem (OMP).",
    "What makes the HP hard is not just that you can only observe doings but not feelings.",
    "It is much more about the apparent causal superfluousness of feeling.",
    "You are right that grounding (through Turing-Testing and causal modelling) cannot explain or even test feeling, but it's not even clear why anything more than doing capacity (T3) would be needed to pass T3 and explain cognitive capacity completely.",
    "And that's true irrespective of the OMP."
  ]
}